text.tspan: GDP per head vs. share of industry in employment, 1800 to 2015
The vertical axis shows historical estimates of the share of industry in employment. The horizontal axis shows
GDP per capita, adjusted for inflation and for differences in the cost of living between countries.
Data source: Our World In Data based on Herrendorf et al. (2014) and GGDC-10 (2015); Our World In Data; Bolt and van Zanden -
Note: GDP per capita is expressed in international-$ at 2011 prices.
